@startuml
title FOR USERS:\nPLR USER SEQUENCE

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 0
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam ParticipantPadding 18
skinparam BoxPadding 8
skinparam ArrowColor black
skinparam LifeLineBorderColor #8a8a8a
skinparam LifeLineBackgroundColor white
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #666666
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor white
skinparam ActorBorderColor #666666
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor white
skinparam SequenceGroupBorderColor black
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor white
skinparam SequenceGroupHeaderFontStyle bold
hide footbox

actor User
participant Frontend
participant Backend
participant "Mail (SMTP)" as Mail
database MongoDB

== 1. USER LOGIN / SIGNUP WITH OTP ==

User -> Frontend : Enter mail and password
Frontend -> Backend : Request OTP
Backend -> MongoDB : Validate details
Backend -> Mail : Send OTP
Mail --> Backend : OTP sent
Backend --> Frontend : OTP response

User -> Frontend : Enter OTP
Frontend -> Backend : Submit OTP
Backend -> MongoDB : Verify OTP
MongoDB --> Backend : Valid / Invalid
Backend --> Frontend : Login result
Frontend --> User : Open workspace

== 2. EMAIL VERIFICATION FLOW ==

User -> Frontend : Request verification
Frontend -> Backend : Verify mail
Backend -> MongoDB : Read / update token
Backend -> Mail : Send link or OTP
Mail --> Backend : Sent
Backend --> Frontend : Verification result

== 3. REVIEW ANALYSIS OPERATION ==

User -> Frontend : Submit review
Frontend -> Backend : Analyze review
Backend -> MongoDB : Read user data
Backend -> Backend : Run analysis
Backend -> MongoDB : Save result
MongoDB --> Backend : Saved
Backend --> Frontend : Result + confidence
Frontend --> User : Show analysis

User -> Frontend : Download report
Frontend -> Backend : Track download
Backend -> MongoDB : Save log

== 4. DASHBOARD / HISTORY ACCESS ==

User -> Frontend : Open dashboard
Frontend -> Backend : Get dashboard
Backend -> MongoDB : Fetch stats
MongoDB --> Backend : Stats data
Backend --> Frontend : Dashboard data

User -> Frontend : Open history
Frontend -> Backend : Get history
Backend -> MongoDB : Fetch reviews
MongoDB --> Backend : History data
Backend --> Frontend : History data

== 5. FEEDBACK / LOGOUT ==

User -> Frontend : Submit feedback
Frontend -> Backend : Send feedback
Backend -> MongoDB : Save feedback

User -> Frontend : Upload file
Frontend -> Backend : Track upload
Backend -> MongoDB : Save upload log

User -> Frontend : Logout
Frontend --> User : Session closed

@enduml
